Although our universe came from very smooth initial conditions, nowadays the diversity of galaxies that we find in the universe is extraordinary. This incredible diversity of galaxies, though, presents a surprising regularity. This fact is manifest in several scaling relations that are shown to hold very tightly for a diverse range of galaxies. These relations relate the dynamical and baryonic properties of galaxies, and hold even for DM-dominated systems, and they are one of the most tantalizing aspects of galaxy phenomenology, representing the most pressing challenge for Λ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\varLambda $$\end{document}CDM on small-scales.

