The GCE is a statistical ensemble that describes a system that is in contact in thermal and chemical equilibrium with a large reservoir, in a way that there is exchange of energy and particles with the reservoir. This exchange of particles with the reservoir makes the number of particles in the system to fluctuate, although the number of particle of the system plus reservoir is constant. As the system is in equilibrium, the energy and particle number fluctuate around an average. This ensemble can be described by the following constants: the chemical potential (μ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
