The description presented above for the superfluid is valid for a zero temperature dilute weakly interacting Bose gas. However, as already described in Landau’s phenomenological theory, for finite temperature system, the superfluid has to be described as a two-fluid model: a mixture of a superfluid and a normal fluid. As we saw previously in this description, for T<Tc\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
