We just want to emphasize one last thing. Bose–Einstein condensation is a quantum mechanical phenomena. It can only arise because of quantum mechanics. The definition of a condensate is the one given in Sect. 3.7. A BEC can be described classically in the classical limit of the many-body theory or the field theory description of a condensate, or by an approximate classical theory as an ensemble of waves like wave turbulence (where we can make a parallel with the definition of a condensate as particles in the ground state which in the language of waves translates is waves with k=0\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
