				\begin{document}$$k=0$$\end{document}).

One of the effects coming from the FDM and SIFDM classes of models is the suppression of small-scale structure. This is a consequence of the fact that these models present sizable Jeans scale which cuts off the structure formation for wavelengths smaller than λJ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
