Specifically for the case of ULDM models, forecasts using 21 cm HI signal were made in Lidz and Hui (2018); Nebrin et al. (2019); Shimabukuro et al. (2020), and they specialize in the FDM model. Lidz and Hui (2018) studied how the recent EDGES measurement of the global 21 cm HI signal (Bowman et al. 2018) can constraint the FDM model. The global signal is the average radio signal from 21 cm redshifted emission from z∼\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
