First, it is interesting to repeat something we presented in Sect. 3.5. The presence of a rotation in a condensate in a spherical halo is that without rotation, the BEC wavefunction is real and positive; however, the angular velocity induces a superfluid current, making the wavefunction to be complex, ψ=|ϕ|eiS(t,r)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
